result.execSummary:
Felicia M Smith was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Felicia M Smith was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Felicia M Smith not in court.  Carole R Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defendant has been turned over to the State of Illinois on January 27, 2014.
On motion of the state, Court ordered case closed.

Defendant Felicia M Smith in court with attorney Mary D Scholle.  Defendant Felicia M Smith in custody.  Danielle E. Chojnacki appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Yamahiro, Branch 34.
Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Illinois.
Defendant waived extradition.  Signed Waiver of Extradition received and filed.
Court ordered the defendant remanded into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  
Case is adjourned for status in ICCR.  Status conference scheduled for February 10, 2014 at 08:30 am.
